en-us:
This includes individuals with two or more of the following conditions:
- Cancer
- Chronic kidney disease
- Chronic lung diseases, including COPD (chronic obstructive pulmonary disease), asthma (moderate-to-severe), interstitial lung disease, cystic fibrosis, and pulmonary hypertension
- Dementia or other neurological conditions
- Diabetes (type 1 or type 2)
- Down syndrome
- Heart conditions (such as heart failure, coronary artery disease, cardiomyopathies or hypertension)
- HIV infection
- Immunocompromised state (weakened immune system)
- Liver disease
- Overweight and obesity
- Pregnancy
- Sickle cell disease or thalassemia
- Smoking, current or former
- Solid organ or blood stem cell transplant
- Stroke or cerebrovascular disease, which affects blood flow to the brain
- Substance use disorders

Individuals 16 and older with one of these certain medical conditions will be eligible to receive the vaccine effective April 5, 2021.
Phase 2 eligible conditions:
Asthma (moderate-to-severe)
Cancer
Chronic kidney disease
COPD (chronic obstructive pulmonary disease)
Down Syndrome
Heart conditions, such as heart failure, coronary artery disease, or cardiomyopathies
Immunocompromised state (weakened immune system) from solid organ transplant*
Obesity and severe obesity (body mass index [BMI] of 30 kg/m2 or higher)
Calculate your BMI here: Adult BMI Calculator | CDC
Pregnancy**
Sickle cell disease
Smoking
Type 2 diabetes mellitus
es-us:
Las personas mayores de 16 años con una de estas ciertas condiciones médicas serán elegibles para recibir la vacuna a partir del 5 de abril de 2021.
Condiciones elegibles para la fase 2:
Asma (de moderada a grave)
Cáncer
Enfermedad renal crónica
EPOC (enfermedad pulmonar obstructiva crónica)
Síndrome de Down
Afecciones cardíacas, como insuficiencia cardíaca, enfermedad de las arterias coronarias o cardiomiopatías
Estado inmunodeprimido (sistema inmunitario debilitado) del trasplante de órganos sólidos*
Obesidad y obesidad grave (índice de masa corporal [IMC] de 30 kg/m2 o superior)
Calcule su IMC aquí: Calculadora de IMC para adultos | CDC
Embarazo**
Enfermedad de células falciformes
Fumar
Diabetes mellitus tipo 2

en-us:
Workers in the following categories are eligible as part of this group:
- Restaurant or cafe workers
- Food, meatpacking, beverage, agriculture, consumer goods, retail, or food service workers
- Grocery and convenience store workers
- Food pantry workers or volunteers
- Medical supply chain workers
- Vaccine development workers
- Transit/transportation workers
- Public works, water, wastewater, or utility workers
- Sanitation workers
- Public health workers
- Court system worker (judges, prosecutors, defense attorneys, clerks), other than court officers who are listed under first responders
- Funeral directors and  funeral workers
es-us:
Los trabajadores de las siguientes categorías son elegibles como parte de este grupo:
- Trabajadores de restaurantes o cafeterías
- Trabajadores de alimentos, envasados de carne, bebidas, agricultura, bienes de consumo, comercio minorista o servicios alimentarios
- Trabajadores de supermercados y tiendas de conveniencia
- Trabajadores de despensas de alimentos o voluntarios
- Trabajadores de la cadena de suministro médica
- Trabajadores de desarrollo de vacunas
- Trabajadores de tránsito/transporte
- Trabajadores de obras públicas, agua, aguas residuales o servicios públicos
- Trabajadores sanitarios
- Trabajadores de salud pública
- Trabajador del sistema judicial (jueces, fiscales, abogados defensores, secretarios), aparte de los funcionarios judiciales que figuran bajo los socorristas
- Directores funerarios y trabajadores funerarios

en-us:
These individuals either:
- Have considerable difficulty and/or require significant support to leave the home for medical appointments
- Require ambulance or two-person assistance to leave the home
- Are not able to leave the home for medical appointments under normal circumstances

If you are eligible for an in-home vaccination, you can call the Homebound Vaccination Central Intake Line at (833) 983-0485.
